    <p>I've been working as a software developer for over 15 years. What started as a hobby with early Macromedia Flash turned into freelance work, then a career building web applications, APIs, and infrastructure.</p>

    <p>I spent several years doing freelance development while touring as a musician — building everything from data-driven touch-screen applications in Flash/ActionScript to corporate CMS sites in PHP/MySQL. In 2009 I moved into a full-time role as a survey programmer and software developer at market research company <a href="http://www.mindwaveresearch.com/">Mindwave Research</a>, where large-scale data projects taught me a deep respect for consistency and validity.</p>

    <p>Discovering Ruby during that time eventually led me to Rails, and I've been working in that world ever since — as a front-end developer, application developer, and on the devops side managing servers and infrastructure.</p>

